<div class="page-header">
  <h1>Window Avatar</h1>
  <p class="lead">Animation and shape parameters for Ferni's signature window avatar system. The window creates the illusion of Ferni peeking through the interface.</p>
</div>

<section class="section" id="concept">
  <h2>The Window Concept</h2>
  <div class="concept-demo">
    <div class="window-avatar-demo">
      <div class="avatar-face">
        <div class="lid top"></div>
        <div class="eye-area"></div>
        <div class="lid bottom"></div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="concept-explanation">
      <p>The avatar appears to peek through a "window" in the UI. The top and bottom lids act as masks that reveal different amounts of the face, creating expressions without changing the eyes themselves.</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Top lid:</strong> Controls brow/forehead visibility</li>
        <li><strong>Bottom lid:</strong> Creates mouth/speaking effect</li>
        <li><strong>Cutoff:</strong> How much of the face is visible</li>
        <li><strong>Curve:</strong> Shape of the mask edge</li>
        <li><strong>Asymmetry:</strong> Left-right difference for expressiveness</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

